unemployed /ˌʌnɪmˈplɔɪd/

1. ADJ Someone who is unemployed does not have a job. 失业的 

例： The problem is millions of people are unemployed. 问题是成百万的人失业。 

例： This workshop helps young unemployed people. 这个讲习班帮助失业的年轻人。 

2. N-PLURAL The unemployed are people who are unemployed. 失业者 

例： We want to create jobs for the unemployed. 我们想为失业者创造更多的工作。

